<subSubSection id="569B8F0BE897F3B73DE16D02C4719907" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="B79167831F14A0AB4B890D5396D53133" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5C2F6ACE5F6155FDF41FABEA414DF732" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">
The buff-yellow pore surface, darkening when touched or bruised, the small pores (6-9 per mm) sometimes with white tomentum, and the ellipsoid small basidiospores (3.1-4.2 
<normalizedToken id="29CFD5F7A3E6D85671697C7982E0B639" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-2.8 
<normalizedToken id="6F9358C4EA9E0A07CA4BC1DF272837FE" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) set this species apart from others in 
<taxonomicName id="FAD26D126A1E560AA9EC48916B6E0F19" authorityName="P.A.Karsten" authorityYear="1879" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Bjerkandera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Bjerkandera" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="84F1CA35BF6D0352167150C7D7C19880" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Bjerkandera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="9A296A9A4975BEE891755441673CD7E3" authorityName="Motato-Vasq., Robledo &amp; Gugliotta" authorityYear="2020" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Bjerkandera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Bjerkandera albocinerea" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="albocinerea">
